 change single new piece music can take several months before completed Men and women usually perform separate groups with the exception Java the pesindhen the female singer who performs with male groups the twentyfive countries outside Indonesia that have gamelan music performed concert context part ceremonies for expat communities may also accompany dance wayang The tuning and construction gamelan orchestra complex process Javanese gamelan use two tuning systems slndro and plog There are other tuning systems such degung exclusive Sunda West Java and madenda also known diatonis similar European natural minor scale central Javanese gamelan slndro system with five notes the octave with large intervals while plog has seven notes the octave with uneven intervals usually played five note subsets the seventone collection full gamelan will include set instruments each tuning and classically only one tuning used time The precise tuning used differs from ensemble ensemble and gives each ensemble its own particular flavour set gamelan instruments will tuned the same set notes but the tuning will vary from one gamelan the next including variations the size intervals Colin McPhee Canadian composer who spent much time Bali remarked Deviations what considered the same scale are large that one might with reason state that there are many scales there are gamelans This view contested however some teachers gamelan and there have been efforts combine multiple ensembles and tuning structures into one gamelan ease transportation festival time One such ensemble gamelan Manikasanti which can play the repertoire many different ensembles Balinese gamelan instruments are built pairs that are tuned slightly apart produce interference beats ideally consistent speed for all pairs notes all registers This concept referred ombak translating wave communicating the idea cyclical undulation One instrument tuned slightly higher thought the inhale and the other slightly lower called the exhale Also called the blower and the sucker pengimbang and pengisep Bali When the inhale and the exhale are combined beating produced meant represent the beating the heart the symbol being alive thought that this contributes the shimmering sound Balinese gamelan ensembles the religious ceremonies that contain gamelan these interference beats are meant give the listener feeling gods presence stepping stone meditative state The scale roughly approximates that the phrygian mode the Western major scale the white keys the piano with the notes EFGBC corresponding the note positions 12356 the slendro scale used most gamelan well the nonwestern octave and the use beats Javanese gamelan uses combination tempo and density known Irama relating how many beats the saron panerus instrument there are notes the core melody balungan density considered primary Gamelan music traditionally not notated and began oral tradition the 19th century however the kraton palaces Yogyakarta and Surakarta developed distinct notations for transcribing the repertoire These were not used read the music which was memorized but preserve pieces the court records The Yogyanese notation checkerboard notation which uses six seven vertical lines represent notes higher pitch the balungan melodic framework and horizontal lines which represent the series beats read downward with time The fourth vertical line and every fourth horizontal line completing gatra are darkened for legibility Symbols the left indicate the colotomic metric structure gongs and forth while specific drum features are notated symbols the right The Solonese notation reads horizontally like Western notation but does not use barlines Instead note values and rests are squiggled between the notes Today this notation relatively rare and has been replaced kepatihan notation which cipher system Kepatihan notation developed around 1900 the kepatihan Palace Surakarta which had become highschool conservatory The pitches are numbered see the articles the scales slendro and plog for explanation how and are read across with dots below above the numbers indicating the register and lines above notes showing time values vocal notation there are also brackets under groups notes indicate melisma Like the palace notation however Kepatihan records mostly the balungan part and its metric phrases marked variety gongs The other parts are created real time and depend the knowledge each musician has his instrument and his awareness what others are playing this realization sometimes called garap Some teachers have also devised certain notations generally using kepatihan principles for the cengkok melodic patterns the elaborating instruments Some ethnomusicologists trained European music may make transcriptions onto Western staff This entails particular challenges tuning and time sometimes resulting unusual clefs The gamelan has been appreciated several western composers classical music most famously Claude Debussy who heard Javanese gamelan the premiere LouisAlbert BourgaultDucoudrays Rhapsodie Cambodgienne the Paris Exposition 1889 Worlds Fair The work had been written seven years earlier 1882 but received its premiere only 1889 The gamelan Debussy heard was the slendro scale and was played Central Javanese musicians Despite his enthusiasm direct citations gamelan scales melodies rhythms ensemble textures have not been located any Debussys own compositions However the equaltempered whole tone scale appears his music this time and afterward and Javanese gamelanlike heterophonic texture emulated occasion particularly Pagodes from Estampes solo piano 1903 which the great gongs cyclic punctuation symbolized prominent perfect fifth The composer Erik Satie influential contemporary Debussy also heard the Javanese gamelan play the Paris Exposition 1889 The repetitively hypnotic effects the gamelan were incorporated into Saties exotic Gnossienne set for piano Direct homages gamelan music are found works for western instruments John Cage particula